w they judge their own children's fathers, including the issue of older boyfriends impregnating teenage girls. The young women's thoughts on the stigma they experience and the transformations in their lives and relationships are illuminating and important to all who care about teenage girls as well as about teenage mothers and their children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aTeenage motherszUnited States. 0aTeenage parentszUnited States. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aSociology : Family Studies. 4aSociology : Social Problems. 4aSociology : Sociology of Women. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842887140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438428871423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438428871/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles